items.title: Private payrolls rose 41,000 in December, slightly below expectations, ADP says
items.description: Private sector job creation turned positive in December though at a bit softer pace than expected.

items.title: Euro zone inflation hits 2% in December, in line with forecasts
items.description: Euro zone inflation stood at 2% in December, flash data from Eurostat showed on Wednesday.

items.title: Economist Mark Zandi sees the Fed surprising with three rate cuts in first half of 2026
items.description: Markets and Fed officials themselves see only modest easing in the year ahead.

items.title: Gas prices fall to four-year lows as millions embark on holiday road trips
items.description: The average price of unleaded gasoline in the U.S. is at its lowest since 2021, according to AAA.

items.title: Trust these numbers? Economists see a lot of flaws in delayed CPI report showing downward inflation
items.description: Thursday saw the release of a much lighter-than-expected inflation report for November, and economists are already questioning its significance.
